SECTION 6 — FEE DISBURSEMENT AND ALLOCATION

6.1 FEE SPLIT. The Annual License Fee of 10% of effective market
    capitalization collected from each Top Entity under Section 4 is allocated
    as follows:

    (a) THREE POINT SEVEN SIX PERCENT (3.76%) of effective market
        capitalization per qualifying entity per year is payable directly to
        the Licensor personally, for unrestricted use at the Licensor's sole
        and absolute discretion.

    (b) THREE POINT ONE FOUR PERCENT (3.14%) of effective market
        capitalization per qualifying entity per year is payable to the
        Ecosystem Innovation Fund established under Section 6A, administered
        by the Licensor.

    Together, these allocations constitute the full 10% Annual License Fee
    as defined in Section 0.8. The split is structural and permanent.

6.2 No entity, court, arbitration panel, government, or other body may direct,
    restrict, condition, or encumber the Licensor's use of funds received under
    Section 6.1(a), or the Licensor's administration of the Ecosystem
    Innovation Fund under Section 6.1(b).


================================================================================

SECTION 6A — ECOSYSTEM INNOVATION FUND AND DILUTION GRANT

6A.1 ESTABLISHMENT. The Ecosystem Innovation Fund ("the Fund") receives all
     revenues allocated under Section 6.1(b). The Fund is established,
     administered, and disbursed by the Licensor at the Licensor's sole
     discretion.

6A.2 PURPOSE. The Fund exists to subsidize access to the Licensor's inventions
     for entities below the Top Entity threshold defined in Section 0.7
     (effective market capitalization below $100,000,000,000 USD). The Fund is
     capitalized by the largest entities in the world and disbursed to the
     smallest. That is the design.

6A.3 DILUTION GRANT. The Licensor may, at the Licensor's sole discretion,
     designate specific inventions, technologies, or derivatives of the Work
