19B.5 ANTI-AGGREGATION. Multiple law firms coordinated by, engaged by, or
      funded by a single Top Entity to collectively handle matters adverse to
      the Licensor are treated as a single qualifying entity for threshold
      purposes. Aggregate gross annual revenue controls. Each firm remains
      individually liable for its own separate Annual License Fee in addition
      to the joint and several liability under Section 19B.2(c).

19B.6 FEE MULTIPLIER. The fee multiplier in Section 4.3 applies to qualifying
      law firms on identical terms. A firm that fails to pay within 90 days of
      first qualifying incurs the compounding multiplier. A firm that takes on
      a representation described in Section 19B.3 after failing to pay incurs
      an additional x3 multiplier on its own fee, per representation.

19B.7 SAFE HARBOR FOR PLAINTIFF-SIDE REPRESENTATION. A qualifying law firm
      that exclusively represents the Licensor in proceedings arising under
      this License -- and does not simultaneously represent any adverse Top
      Entity -- is exempt from the Annual License Fee for any year in which
      it provides such exclusive representation. The exemption applies only
      to years of exclusive Licensor-side service and does not retroactively
      reduce prior-year fee obligations.


